Because I felt bad.

516
00:32:00,523 --> 00:32:02,275
I'm sure you remember too.

517
00:32:02,942 --> 00:32:07,155
There was a case two years ago
where a teacher was murdered at school

518
00:32:07,238 --> 00:32:08,448
by their own student.

519
00:32:09,365 --> 00:32:12,285
I thought teachers' rights
needed to be clearly established

520
00:32:12,368 --> 00:32:14,162
so nothing like that happens again.

521
00:32:14,245 --> 00:32:15,997
But why Daehan High of all places?

522
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:18,374
My son is suffering
because of it right now.

523
00:32:19,542 --> 00:32:21,711
Does your son go to Daehan High?

524
00:32:23,463 --> 00:32:24,547
Oh dear.

525
00:32:26,007 --> 00:32:27,717
The inspector has been going too far.

526
00:32:27,800 --> 00:32:30,553
If this is publicized,
public criticism will grow fierce.

527
00:32:30,636 --> 00:32:32,388
Nothing good can come from this.

528
00:32:32,472 --> 00:32:34,348
So why don't you just end it here?

529
00:32:37,351 --> 00:32:40,480
Well, there are a lot of eyes on us,

530
00:32:40,563 --> 00:32:43,399
and the organization
has just been established.

531
00:32:43,483 --> 00:32:45,777
How about we just wait a little longer?

532
00:32:45,860 --> 00:32:48,529
You know I have respect for you, Minister.

533
00:32:49,697 --> 00:32:51,908
I'm telling you all this for your sake.

534
00:32:51,991 --> 00:32:55,536
You wouldn't want to retire from politics
over something like this.

535
00:33:01,626 --> 00:33:03,419
A father would do anything

536
00:33:04,337 --> 00:33:05,922
for his child.

537
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:19,560
This is Ryu Gwang-pil
of the Happiness Hope Party.

538
00:33:19,644 --> 00:33:21,437
Please support him.

539
00:33:22,063 --> 00:33:23,648
-Thank you.
-What's the time?

540
00:33:24,148 --> 00:33:25,525
Shouldn't he be here by now?

541
00:33:26,025 --> 00:33:28,736
-Come on, set your phones to vibrate.
-Sorry.

542
00:33:28,820 --> 00:33:31,572
<i>People as People, Politics as Politics</i>.

543
00:33:31,656 --> 00:33:34,325
What's this?
"Using aides for personal matters"?

544
00:33:34,408 --> 00:33:37,411
"Bribery in exchange
for local election nomination"?

545
00:33:38,121 --> 00:33:40,498
-Sexual harassment?
-What's this about?

546
00:33:40,581 --> 00:33:45,962
Ryu Gwang-pil!

547
00:33:46,045 --> 00:33:47,880
Thank you for taking the time to come.

548
00:33:47,964 --> 00:33:50,550
Do you admit to the bribery allegations?

549
00:33:50,633 --> 00:33:52,760
-What do you mean?
-There has been a tip-off.

550
00:33:52,844 --> 00:33:54,387
It's about your sexual misconduct.

551
00:33:54,971 --> 00:33:57,723
Is it true that you engaged
in illegal property speculation?

552
00:33:57,807 --> 00:33:59,183
What the hell is going on?

553
00:33:59,267 --> 00:34:00,977
I'll look into it. You should go.

554
00:34:01,060 --> 00:34:03,563
-Hurry and block them off here!
-Don't push!

555
00:34:03,646 --> 00:34:05,481
Do you admit it? Please say something!

556
00:34:05,565 --> 00:34:06,983
Assemblyman Ryu!

557
00:34:09,193 --> 00:34:10,528
Damn it.

558
00:34:48,357 --> 00:34:49,775
What's going on?

559
00:34:49,859 --> 00:34:51,235
It's noisy out there.

560
00:34:51,319 --> 00:34:52,945
There's no need for you to know.

561
00:34:53,696 --> 00:34:55,406
It'd be best if you left now.

562
00:34:57,366 --> 00:35:00,912
You must be a little slow on the uptake.

563
00:35:11,923 --> 00:35:12,882
Don't tell me

564
00:35:14,467 --> 00:35:16,177
you're behind this?

565
00:35:16,677 --> 00:35:18,888
Who put you up to this?

566
00:35:27,980 --> 00:35:29,941
It took me two years…

567
00:35:31,901 --> 00:35:33,277
to create the ERPB.

568
00:35:34,570 --> 00:35:35,821
It turns out

569
00:35:36,447 --> 00:35:38,407
two years is quite a long time.

570
00:35:49,210 --> 00:35:51,712
RYU GWANG-PIL
UNOFFICIAL REPORT

571
00:35:53,464 --> 00:35:54,966
RECORDING OF VICTIM INTERVIEW

572
00:35:59,220 --> 00:36:01,180
RYU GWANG-PIL
NOMINATION CORRUPTION REPORT

573
00:36:05,268 --> 00:36:06,394
<i>Are you crazy?</i>

574
00:36:06,477 --> 00:36:08,980
You and I are on the same side!

575
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:12,233
We're in the same party, for fuck's sake!

576
00:36:12,316 --> 00:36:13,317
Assemblyman Ryu.

577
00:36:14,068 --> 00:36:17,405
There is no such thing as sides
when it comes to education.

578
00:36:17,488 --> 00:36:19,991
Was I your target from the very beginning?

579
00:36:20,074 --> 00:36:21,158
Just why?

580
00:36:21,242 --> 00:36:23,035
What the hell have I done so wrong?

581
00:36:23,619 --> 00:36:25,413
Are you serious or full of baloney?

582
00:36:26,205 --> 00:36:29,041
Your wrongdoings
should be all over the news by now.

583
00:36:31,460 --> 00:36:33,296
Shit, this is fucked up!

584
00:36:33,838 --> 00:36:36,173
There are so many people
worse than me out there!

585
00:36:36,674 --> 00:36:39,051
So why the hell are you doing this to me?

586
00:36:47,310 --> 00:36:49,562
That's because

587
00:36:50,521 --> 00:36:51,939
when you fall,

588
00:36:53,274 --> 00:36:54,859
your son falls too.

589
00:37:00,489 --> 00:37:04,785
You really should've educated
that brat of yours better.

590
00:37:17,214 --> 00:37:18,758
-Minister.
-Please step aside.

591
00:37:21,927 --> 00:37:23,137
Damn it!

592
00:37:23,220 --> 00:37:24,847
-Are you there?
-Sir!

593
00:37:25,848 --> 00:37:26,891
Just a moment!

594
00:37:26,974 --> 00:37:30,644
<i>The National Assembly approved</i>
<i>an arrest motion of Ryu Gwang-pil,</i>

595
00:37:30,728 --> 00:37:32,229
<i>who faces corruption allegations.</i>

596
00:37:32,813 --> 00:37:35,274
<i>Furthermore, there have been allegations</i>

597
00:37:35,358 --> 00:37:37,902
<i>that Ryu's son was responsible</i>
<i>for the school bullying</i>

598
00:37:37,985 --> 00:37:40,237
<i>that resulted</i>
<i>in the death of his classmate,</i>

599
00:37:40,321 --> 00:37:41,822
<i>shocking the public even more.</i>

600
00:37:41,906 --> 00:37:44,325
<i>This case, which almost got buried,</i>

601
00:37:44,408 --> 00:37:47,161
<i>surfaced through an investigation</i>
<i>by the ERPB.</i>

602
00:37:47,244 --> 00:37:51,457
<i>The ERPB, a new agency</i>
<i>led by the Minister of Education,</i>

603
00:37:51,540 --> 00:37:54,919
<i>will handle the independent</i>
<i>and prompt protection of teachers' rights.</i>

604
00:37:55,002 --> 00:37:58,339
<i>It is responsible for receiving reports,</i>
<i>investigating, and responding--</i>

605
00:38:01,008 --> 00:38:03,677
This might also turn
into a political issue.

606
00:38:04,345 --> 00:38:05,388
Would you be okay?

607
00:38:05,471 --> 00:38:08,265
I'll take all the bullets and missiles.

608
00:38:08,974 --> 00:38:10,351
You just get the job done.

609
00:38:13,145 --> 00:38:15,398
Like you've ever been shot.

610
00:38:16,148 --> 00:38:18,818
If you get shot,
you'll actually die of pain.

611
00:38:20,069 --> 00:38:21,779
It's just a metaphor.

612
00:38:23,572 --> 00:38:24,740
I won't really take it.

613
00:38:24,824 --> 00:38:26,492
I was using a metaphor too.

614
00:38:26,575 --> 00:38:28,035
Thank you for your effort.

615
00:38:39,839 --> 00:38:41,966
Hey, did you guys see this?

616
00:38:42,049 --> 00:38:44,885
As of today, the Daehan High outcast is…

617
00:38:44,969 --> 00:38:47,805
Cutie Pie! Applause!

618
00:38:48,597 --> 00:38:50,891
Hey, it looks best on you so far.

619
00:38:54,645 --> 00:38:56,897
Our dear Jun-hyeong, where are you going?

620
00:38:57,398 --> 00:39:00,109
He's fucking nothing without his dad!

621
00:39:00,192 --> 00:39:01,735
It stinks like trash.

622
00:39:02,903 --> 00:39:06,031
OUTCAST STICK

623
00:39:52,620 --> 00:39:54,079
It's not your fault.

624
00:40:03,047 --> 00:40:04,131
Gyeong-min.

625
00:40:06,675 --> 00:40:08,093
It's not your fault.

626
00:40:17,561 --> 00:40:19,730
When Dae-seok became the outcast,

627
00:40:21,273 --> 00:40:22,942
I was relieved.

628
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:25,694
When he died,

629
00:40:26,862 --> 00:40:28,364
I couldn't help but smile.

630
00:40:30,950 --> 00:40:34,119
I thought I'd be able to break free
from this hell.

631
00:40:38,999 --> 00:40:41,293
I'm no different from them.

632
00:40:44,588 --> 00:40:46,090
Yes, you are, kiddo.

633
00:40:47,925 --> 00:40:49,969
You were picked on for no reason.

634
00:40:50,678 --> 00:40:52,846
Those who bullied you

635
00:40:53,597 --> 00:40:57,309
and the adults who knew but silenced you
are the ones at fault.

636
00:40:57,935 --> 00:41:00,354
So don't be regretful

637
00:41:01,105 --> 00:41:02,314
or feel remorseful.

638
00:41:37,349 --> 00:41:39,435
-He's crazy!
-Fuck this!

639
00:41:39,518 --> 00:41:42,104
I recorded everything, you motherfucker.

640
00:41:42,605 --> 00:41:44,481
Die, you fucking bastards.

641
00:41:45,065 --> 00:41:46,275
Jun-hyeong!

642
00:41:46,358 --> 00:41:48,360
Jun-hyeong, I'm sorry!

643
00:41:48,444 --> 00:41:49,612
Jun-hyeong!

644
00:41:52,114 --> 00:41:53,407
Fuck this!

645
00:41:58,203 --> 00:41:59,580
-The ERPB is here.
-It's him.

646
00:41:59,663 --> 00:42:01,040
We're safe now.

647
00:42:01,624 --> 00:42:03,125
You just can't own up, can you?

648
00:42:08,797 --> 00:42:09,965
I told you, didn't I?

649
00:42:10,049 --> 00:42:13,552
Remorse is something you do
with your body, not your mind.

650
00:42:17,306 --> 00:42:18,140
Are you crazy?

651
00:42:18,223 --> 00:42:19,850
The gasoline.

652
00:42:20,434 --> 00:42:21,435
What about it?

653
00:42:25,272 --> 00:42:26,649
Isn't this why you poured it?

654
00:43:04,603 --> 00:43:07,898
Please help me! I'm sorry!

655
00:43:09,566 --> 00:43:10,859
I was wrong!

656
00:43:11,568 --> 00:43:13,821
Please help me!

657
00:43:20,077 --> 00:43:21,662
Please help me!

658
00:43:21,745 --> 00:43:23,580
It's all my fault.

659
00:43:23,664 --> 00:43:25,874
I'm sorry!

660
00:43:45,436 --> 00:43:48,605
Why the hell are you taking it
this far with me? Why?

661
00:43:49,189 --> 00:43:50,357
And what about you?

662
00:43:51,275 --> 00:43:53,652
Why did you take it so far with Dae-seok?

663
00:44:01,744 --> 00:44:03,954
Dae-seok was afraid of dying too.

664
00:44:04,496 --> 00:44:05,330
Just like you.

665
00:44:07,541 --> 00:44:09,251
But he still made that choice

666
00:44:09,752 --> 00:44:12,045
because of a scumbag like you.

667
00:44:14,173 --> 00:44:18,177
WITH VIGOR, HOLDING HOPEFUL DREAMS CLOSE

668
00:44:25,142 --> 00:44:27,853
<i>If you're finding the bullying</i>
<i>so difficult to deal with,</i>

669
00:44:27,936 --> 00:44:29,772
how about moving to a different school?

670
00:44:29,855 --> 00:44:32,608
Excuse me?
Why should my child move to a new school?

671
00:44:33,650 --> 00:44:37,571
<i>The bully should switch schools.</i>
<i>Why should the victim go?</i>

672
00:44:40,324 --> 00:44:43,619
You can't just cancel your order
all of a sudden like this.

673
00:44:43,702 --> 00:44:46,955
I just don't understand what's going on
with our vendors.

674
00:44:48,874 --> 00:44:50,083
I'm sorry.

675
00:44:50,167 --> 00:44:51,835
-Please go easy on my dad.
-Get lost.

676
00:44:51,919 --> 00:44:53,504
-Shut up.
-Ask your dad.

677
00:44:53,587 --> 00:44:55,547
Ask him to go easy on my dad
this one time.

678
00:44:55,631 --> 00:44:59,343
Why are you asking me?
I'm just a helpless jerk without my dad.

679
00:44:59,426 --> 00:45:00,803
I'm really sorry.

680
00:45:00,886 --> 00:45:04,389
What can I do to make it up to you?
I'll do whatever you say.

681
00:45:06,892 --> 00:45:08,268
Go fucking die, then.

682
00:45:32,417 --> 00:45:35,462
Making the students
realize the full extent of their actions

683
00:45:35,546 --> 00:45:39,049
by giving them
a taste of their own medicine

684
00:45:39,132 --> 00:45:41,885
and making them take responsibility
for those actions.

685
00:45:42,427 --> 00:45:44,721
This is the true education…

686
00:45:46,807 --> 00:45:48,767
that the ERPB seeks.

687
00:45:59,444 --> 00:46:01,780
But no matter what you do to make amends…

688
00:46:04,408 --> 00:46:06,577
Dae-seok
can never be brought back to life.

689
00:46:08,787 --> 00:46:12,082
The least you can do is carry that burden
for the rest of your life.

690
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:15,502
That's the only way to make it fair.

691
00:46:21,592 --> 00:46:23,343
This is the hell you created.

692
00:46:23,427 --> 00:46:25,012
See how you like living there.

693
00:46:41,194 --> 00:46:43,697
<i>The police reopened Dae-seok's case</i>

694
00:46:43,780 --> 00:46:46,825
<i>and arrested those who bullied Dae-seok,</i>
<i>including Ryu Jun-hyeong.</i>

695
00:46:46,909 --> 00:46:49,328
You told me to trust you,
you fucking bitch!

696
00:46:49,411 --> 00:46:50,621
<i>And for the first time…</i>

697
00:46:50,704 --> 00:46:51,663
He's not here.

698
00:46:51,747 --> 00:46:54,041
<i>…the principal took accountability</i>
<i>like a grown-up.</i>

699
00:46:54,124 --> 00:46:55,626
-I said he's not here.
-Mr. Kim!

700
00:46:55,709 --> 00:46:57,169
What are you doing down there?

701
00:46:58,295 --> 00:47:00,255
<i>On the ERPB website,</i>

702
00:47:00,339 --> 00:47:03,842
<i>Ryu Jun-hyeong's bullying</i>
<i>was made public for everyone to see.</i>

703
00:47:07,596 --> 00:47:11,475
<i>And they say those records</i>
<i>will never be erased</i>

704
00:47:11,558 --> 00:47:13,769
<i>unless the victims forgive them.</i>

705
00:47:17,689 --> 00:47:20,984
<i>That was how the ERPB</i>
<i>ended their guidance at Daehan High.</i>

706
00:47:26,531 --> 00:47:30,327
<i>After that day, we never saw</i>
<i>the inspector at school again.</i>

707
00:48:38,937 --> 00:48:41,398
THE LATE CHOI GA-YUN
1995.07.25 - 2024.11.27

708
00:48:41,481 --> 00:48:43,775
WE WILL NOT FORGET

709
00:50:33,802 --> 00:50:38,807
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

